    %h1 About

    %p
      %a.pull-right{:href => 'http://www.smartchicagocollaborative.org'}
        %img(src="/assets/logo_smartchicago.png")
      The Chicago Health Atlas is a Web site for displaying aggregate health-related information on a map so that people can see the prevalence of specific health conditions in their area and find out how they can improve their health. 

    %p
      The 
      %a{:href => 'http://www.smartchicagocollaborative.org'}Smart Chicago Collabrative 
      is working with the 
      %a{:href => 'http://www.cityofchicago.org/city/en/depts/cdph.html'} Chicago Department of Public Health 
      and five local hospitals through 
      %a{:href => 'http://chitrec.org/'} Chicago Health Information Technology Regional Extension (CHITREC) 
      to 
      %a{:href => 'http://www.cityofchicago.org/city/en/depts/cdph/provdrs/pol_plan_report/svcs/office_of_epidemiologydataanalysisrequests.html?cq_ck=1338570736462'} visualize statistics related to public health 
      along with anonymized diagnoses, medications, and laboratory tests as provided by local healthcare institutions. The project is funded by the 
      = succeed '.' do
        %a{:href => 'http://www.spragueinstitute.org/'} Otho S. A. Sprague Memorial Institute
    %hr
    %h3#about-the-data About the data

    %p
      We currently have three types of data on the Health Atlas:

    %ol
      %li
        = succeed '.' do
          %a{:href => 'http://www.cityofchicago.org/city/en/depts/cdph/provdrs/pol_plan_report/svcs/office_of_epidemiologydataanalysisrequests.html'} Statistics related to public health in Chicago
        We obtain this information from the 
        = succeed '.' do
          %a{:href => 'http://www.cityofchicago.org/city/en/depts/cdph/provdrs/pol_plan_report/svcs/office_of_epidemiologydataanalysisrequests.html'}City of Chicagoâ€™s Open Data Portal
        The data is provided by the Chicago Department of Public Health's Epidemiology & Public Health Informatics Program
      %li
        Anonymized clinical diagnosis information provided by CHITREC and its partners. Details on this data was presented at the 
        = succeed '.' do
          %a{:href => 'http://www.amia.org/amia2012/theater-style-demonstration'} American Medical Informatics Association (AMIA) National Symposium here in Chicago on November 6
        See the 
        = succeed '.' do
          %a{:href => 'http://www.smartchicagocollaborative.org/projects/chicago-health-atlas/'} Smart Chicago project page for a description of that talk
      %li
        Data about clinics, programs, and other health resources that can be of use to people who want to improve their health. Most of this information is taken from the City's 
        = succeed ',' do
          %a{:href => 'https://data.cityofchicago.org/'} Open Data Portal
        but we are open to other data types.
    
